results.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Dec. 22 (UPI) The National Aeronautics and Space Administration today named six Americans, including a woman, as finalists for one of two scientist seats aboard the first Spacelab, a science laboratory to be orbited in the cargo bay of the space shuttle in March 1980.
